[32m# Project Tracker Architecture[0m
[32m[0m
[32m## Chosen approach[0m
[32m[0m
[32mBuild a single Django project under `apps/project-tracker/` with one primary Django app for the product domain. Use server-rendered templates as the default UI surface and small asynchronous interactions for create, edit, and delete flows so the page does not fully reload.[0m
[32m[0m
[32m## Proposed structure[0m
[32m[0m
[32m- `apps/project-tracker/manage.py`[0m
[32m- `apps/project-tracker/project_tracker/`[0m
[32m  - `settings.py`, `urls.py`, `asgi.py`, `wsgi.py`[0m
[32m- `apps/project-tracker/tracker/`[0m
[32m  - `models.py`[0m
[32m  - `forms.py`[0m
[32m  - `views.py`[0m
[32m  - `urls.py`[0m
[32m  - `admin.py`[0m
[32m  - `tests/`[0m
[32m- `apps/project-tracker/templates/tracker/`[0m
[32m  - `base.html`[0m
[32m  - `dashboard.html`[0m
[32m  - `project_list.html`[0m
[32m  - `project_detail.html`[0m
[32m  - `tag_detail.html`[0m
[32m  - `partials/`[0m
[32m- `apps/project-tracker/static/tracker/`[0m
[32m  - `app.css`[0m
[32m  - `app.js`[0m
[32m[0m
[32m## Domain boundaries[0m
[32m[0m
[32m- `Project`: name, description, status, created_date, tags.[0m
[32m- `Task`: project, title, status, priority, due_date, tags.[0m
[32m- `Tag`: label/name shared by projects and tasks through many-to-many relations.[0m
[32m[0m
[32mKeep business rules near models and forms. Avoid service layers unless repeated logic becomes concrete.[0m
[32m[0m
[32m## View and endpoint strategy[0m
[32m[0m
[32m- Full-page GET views:[0m
[32m  - dashboard summary[0m
[32m  - project list[0m
[32m  - project detail with related tasks[0m
[32m  - tag filter/detail view[0m
[32m- Mutation endpoints:[0m
[32m  - create, update, delete for projects[0m
[32m  - create, update, delete for tasks[0m
[32m  - create, update, delete for tags[0m
[32m[0m
[32mEach mutation should return either:[0m
[32m[0m
[32m- an HTML partial for the updated list/detail region, or[0m
[32m- a small JSON envelope only when the client needs minimal status data to drive a targeted DOM update.[0m
[32m[0m
[32mDefault to HTML partial responses because they keep rendering rules on the server and reduce duplicated template logic in JavaScript.[0m
[32m[0m
[32m## Frontend interaction model[0m
[32m[0m
[32mUse vanilla JavaScript with event delegation and `fetch` for form submissions and destructive actions. Mark asynchronously enhanced forms and buttons with explicit data attributes. The server remains the source of truth for rendered markup; JavaScript only swaps returned fragments into the DOM and handles lightweight error display.[0m
[32m[0m
[32m## Data and querying[0m
[32m[0m
[32m- SQLite is the only persistence layer.[0m
[32m- Use straightforward Django ORM queries.[0m
[32m- Dashboard counts should be direct aggregate queries:[0m
[32m  - total projects[0m
[32m  - tasks by status[0m
[32m  - overdue tasks where due_date is before today and status is not `done`[0m
[32m[0m
[32mDo not add caching, background jobs, or analytics infrastructure.[0m
[32m[0m
[32m## Tradeoffs[0m
[32m[0m
[32m- One Django app is preferred over multiple apps because the domain is small and tightly related.[0m
[32m- HTML partials are preferred over a broad JSON API because the product is server-rendered and CRUD-focused.[0m
[32m- Forms provide validation and error rendering with less custom code than handwritten request parsing.[0m
[32m- Keep URLs explicit instead of introducing generic viewsets or abstraction-heavy CRUD helpers.[0m
[32m[0m
[32m## Risks to watch[0m
